The paper proposes a new algorithm for discrete integration, which is a fundamental problem in machine learning and probabilistic inference. The algorithm is designed to be efficient and adaptive, and it achieves good results on a variety of benchmarks. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), and systems and control (cs.SY).
